    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-main">
        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="card-section-title">What It Is</h2>
          <p>A community operated mesh radio network intended to provide back-up or even daily text communications, using small inexpensive hardware. All Salish Mesh infrastructure operates entirely on solar power.</p>
          <p>Our friends at <a href="https://pugetmesh.org/" class="ext-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PugetMesh<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14 21 3"/></svg></a> are linked to our mesh — making us one big cross-border family. The network operates on <a href="https://meshcore.io/" class="ext-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MeshCore<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14 21 3"/></svg></a> firmware.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
          <h2 class="card-section-title">What It Isn't</h2>
          <p>A replacement for the internet, cellphones, or satellite emergency communications. It's a resilient supplement — for when those fail.</p>
        </div>

